title: For Sale:  Backpack & boots
postcontent: WHO AM I KIDDING?  I got these boots and backpack when I was thinking I was going to go hunting in Colorado, and I haven't been hunting in five years.  They are good products from Cabela's, but I no longer remember the exact time when I bought them.The back pack is an external frame pack that is well thought out and made of first class materials.  I know -- I used to hike in the Sierras with a Kelty pack when they first came on the market (bought it from Kelty himself out of his garage in Glendale), and I know well designed hiking equipment when I see it.  This is top of the line, with outside zipper pockets for all the stuff you might want on the trail and large cargo space for stuff you will get out in camp.  Light weight, never used, cost $150+ bought new.  Boots are desert tan tactical boots, Size 11.  Just the thing, I thought, for hunting everything from antelope to elk in NV.  But I haven't drawn a tag the past three years and probably won't even apply next year.  Strong, sturdy boots, zip-up lacing, I wore them once after paying $159 for them  The pack frame is too large to ship, so I prefer to sell face-to-face in the Reno area.  I'll come to you with them if you're in the Reno-Silver Springs-Topaz triangle, maybe even further.  Cash payment only.$110 for each, or make me a reasonable cash offer.  Give your hunting buddy or yourself a nice Christmas present!  Priced for quick sale.  Quality merchandise at a reasonable price.
